<TITLE> BNP starts marking Zia's death anniversary May 25 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 6 (bdnews24.com) BNP has decided programmes marking the 28th death anniversary of the party founder former president Ziaur Rahman on May 30, a senior leader said on Wednesday. The party at a meeting chaired by secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain at the central office in Dhaka formed a national committee led by vice president MK Anwar. The programmes starting from May 25 include keeping the party flag at half-mast and flying black flag, discussion sessions, placing wreaths at Zia's grave, prayer sessions and distributing food among the destitute, office secretary Rizvi Ahmed said. The main programmes will be held from May 29 to May 31, he said
